<div id="questionHelpModel" class="modal modal-fixed-footer openlap-help-model">
    <div class="modal-content">
        <h4>Question</h4>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12 openlap-help">
                <table>
                    <tr>
                        <td colspan="2">
                            <span>In this section the core question is formulated which needs to be answered. E.g. a simple LA question can be "How active are students in my courseroom?". To answer this question, the user define a set of indicators and associate them with the question. Following are the three ways how a user can create indicator.</span>
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><a class="btn-floating light-blue darken-2"><i class="material-icons">add</i></a></td>
                        <td><span ><b>New Indicator:</b> Define a new basic indicator from scratch by specifying dataset, applying filter, analyzing and visualizing. More details in the indicator definition section.</span></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><a class="btn-floating green darken-2"><i class="material-icons">file_download</i></a></td>
                        <td><span ><b>Load Indicator:</b> Load exting indicator created by other users and customize it.</span></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><a class="btn-floating yellow darken-2"><i class="material-icons">view_column</i></a></td>
                        <td><span ><b>Composite Indicator:</b> The indicators associated with the current LA question can be combined together to form a composite indicator. Only the indicator which applies the same analysis can be combined together. The composite indicator cannot be loaded for editing (yet). More details in the composite indicator definition section.</span></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><a class="btn-floating red darken-2"><i class="material-icons">view_quilt</i></a></td>
                        <td><span ><b>Multi Level Analysis (MLA) Indicator:</b> Define a new indicator that apply analysis at two levels. Therefore, at first level multiple datasets, filters, and analysis are selected. The results of these analysis are combined and analyzed again before visualizing. More details in the MLA indicator definition section.</span></td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="modal-footer">
        <button class="modal-close waves-effect waves-light btn light-blue darken-2" title="Close the dialog box." >
            Close
        </button>
    </div>
</div>